The `dev` group's parse-time and no-daemon contracts hold without Live (FOUNDATION
surface guarantees, SPEC D §3/§7). These are deterministic on any machine: they never
touch Live, the host, or the socket. As the agents fill in the verbs, the
"not implemented yet" bodies become the real §6.2 transcripts; the EXIT CODES and the
name-vs-verb routing asserted here are the frozen contract.

`register --name` with `--recursive` is rejected at PARSE time (exit 2) — one name
cannot label N members (§3.2).

```
$ rackabel dev register --name foo --recursive
? 2
error: the argument '--name <NAME>' cannot be used with '--recursive'

Usage: rackabel dev register --name <NAME> [PATH]

For more information, try '--help'.

```

A `dev` verb that needs a running daemon, with none up, is an ENVIRONMENT error
(exit 3, RK0309) — never a hang, never a silent default (§7 `--no-input`).

```
$ rackabel dev reload --no-input
? 3
error: `rackabel dev reload` is not implemented yet [RK0309]
  help: this part of the managed dev host (DESIGN §3, milestone 0.3) is still being built
(run `rackabel explain RK0309` for details)

```

A bare token that is NOT a verb routes to the bare loop (the registry name matcher),
not the verb table — `rackabel dev test` is the subcommand, while `rackabel dev --only
test` targets the extension named `test` (the bare loop, exit 3). With nothing
registered and no project in the cwd, `dev test` has nothing to test → `RK0001` (it
routes to the test runner, NOT the bare loop's `RK0307`).

```
$ rackabel dev test --no-input
? 3
error: no manifest found [RK0001]
  --> looked for rackabel.toml in [..] and its parents
  help: run `rackabel new` to scaffold one, or cd into a project directory
(run `rackabel explain RK0001` for details)

```

```
$ rackabel dev --only test --no-input
? 3
error: the bare `rackabel dev` loop is not implemented yet [RK0307]
  help: this part of the managed dev host (DESIGN §3, milestone 0.3) is still being built
(run `rackabel explain RK0307` for details)

```
